# Puja Vidhi

Welcome to the Puja Vidhi repository!

## Purpose

This repo preserves and shares our family’s puja procedures, making them easily accessible anywhere.
It includes step-by-step instructions, rituals, and guidelines to keep traditions alive.

Content: View here

## Local Testing

Run with http-server to preview locally:

```
sudo apt install npm
npm install -g http-server -y
http-server
```

Open this URL [127.0.0.1](http://127.0.0.1:8080) in your browser.

## Tools

LLMs used: [ChatGPT](https://chatgpt.com)  and [Perplexity AI](https://www.perplexity.ai)

Use these to read images or text and convert to kannada:

* [Akshara Mukha Converter](https://www.aksharamukha.com/converter)

* [i2OCR](https://www.i2ocr.com/free-online-telugu-ocr)

For writing kannada text:

* [Akshara Mukha Kannada Input](https://www.aksharamukha.com/input/Kannada) (with svara)
    - use `\_` for anudatta e.g. `ಚಂ॒ದ್ರಾಂ॒`
    - `\'` for swarita e.g. `ಹರಿ॑ಣೀಂ`
    - `\"` for deerga-swarita e.g. `ಮಿನೀ᳚ಮ್`
    - normal kannada text is udatta e.g. `ಶ್ರಿಯಮ್`

* [Lexi Logos Kannada Keyboard](https://www.lexilogos.com/keyboard/kannada.htm)

* [Google Translate](https://www.google.com/search?q=kannada+to+english)

